elements.2211.03171_2ff26fefacb838a2ffcf8b29613ac: R-peak detection is crucial in electrocardiogram (ECG) signal processing as it is the basis of heart rate variability analysis

elements.2211.03171_61d0ee4a085571ecb29d6730ba48c: increase in F-score on average across four datasets, with 33
elements.2211.03171_67196ee22f2b7e668f35fdda18c13: We show specific examples to demonstrate that in situations where the Pan-Tompkins algorithm fails to identify R-peaks, the proposed algorithm is found to be effective
elements.2211.03171_94e9612159da8ecae6bdb8f6dbd48: The results have also been contrasted with other well-known R-peak detection algorithms.
elements.2211.03171_41ebc543770e6592c654d0c370309: R-peak Detection, QRS Complex, Pan-Tompkins Algorithm, Electrocardiogram (ECG).
elements.2211.03171_442c5b59ac75212614b63d6795310: Cardiovascular diseases are the major cause of mortality worldwide, with nearly 17.8 million deaths per year
elements.2211.03171_dec65fae4e43faa2ab31ad8ffa63a: The most commonly utilized cardiovascular disease diagnostic technique is the electrocardiogram (ECG)
elements.2211.03171_0fc1d508046203d4aad995a280cbe: Worldwide, approximately 3 million ECGs are generated every day
elements.2211.03171_100911bb52ed5306ddcb8a6a2fa94: As wearable technology advances, the number of ECGs generated for examination only increases
elements.2211.03171_cc4c4347cddcf6c858162b5c62573: Automated diagnosis techniques are necessary to analyze ECGs produced by wearable technology and to lessen the workload for doctors
elements.2211.03171_a40c593113483bb4aff5741d3aab3: An electrocardiogram (ECG) is a visual representation of the electrical signals produced during a cardiac cycle
elements.2211.03171_fe84902ac4ff687ae8a3a574dedc5: It gives details about the rhythm and morphology of heart rate
elements.2211.03171_65c216605b14b4543c81e87cffd98: Cardiologists utilize ECG to monitor heart conditions and to detect cardiac illnesses such as arrhythmias, hyperkalemia, and myocardial infarction
elements.2211.03171_01de7d1162d14e3d04e898fa4c3aa: A large amount of medical information can be obtained by measuring the amplitudes and durations of the ECG signals
elements.2211.03171_43f36f8e0cf6ca6ca080421edd60c: In order to compute heart rate and detect arrhythmias, R-peak identification in ECG signal is crucial
elements.2211.03171_b646e69bcdfa8830c648158f75091: The ECG signal is made up of various waves, including P-waves, QRS complexes, and T-waves
elements.2211.03171_f4f2ae8583ab4210d5be4fa53a8fe: A QRS complex is a brief-duration pulse that contains an R-peak with a high amplitude
elements.2211.03171_1681982a5504f06b6e47d4232f970: The majority of automatic computer-based solutions concentrate on identifying QRS complexes
elements.2211.03171_534149a2c11c78aff9271d0a2cf8e: Clinically, the accurate identification of the QRS complex is essential
elements.2211.03171_06342e9213a2c284a18c85b9aca8e: Any deviation from the typical ECG sinus rhythm caused by the atria and ventricles depolarizing or repolarizing prematurely or slowly results in a change in the morphology of the QRS, which is further linked to one or more cardiac disorders
elements.2211.03171_49d9aa819508f6e3ed076d7d797a4: The most common technique for QRS detection in commercial devices is the one proposed by Pan and Tompkins
elements.2211.03171_6879a3cccc6da2024f7d4a70475b6: With accurate clinical ECG signal data, this approach offers good detection performance
elements.2211.03171_960f9f86bece39f98659580828f2c: However, low-quality and noisy signals, as well as ambulatory ECG recordings, reduce the Pan-Tompkins algorithm's capacity to detect QRS complexes
elements.2211.03171_1a95f3c632f3b3dcb4dcb0170724e: This study analyzes the limitations of the Pan-Tompkins algorithm
elements.2211.03171_81f91e0593694c1d55820e1859354: We analyze the False Positives and False Negatives given by the Pan-Tompkins, identify the causes behind them, and introduce an efficient algorithm, namely Pan-Tompkins++, that boosts the performance of the original algorithm
elements.2211.03171_d5b005d014202297a3c0319dad85a: We applied a bandpass filter with a passband of 5â18 Hz to remove noise without discarding significant signal components
elements.2211.03171_6e21a00bdba1f5f3c08533d7596ed: An N-point moving average filter has been applied to smooth the signal
elements.2211.03171_3b07dfd1231f86c1704a9a359dcbd: To further deal with noise, three thresholds have been used
elements.2211.03171_6dcf4d103e23fdcc0df0f17ff3ee2: Instead of adjusting them with a generalized equation, they are adjusted by different rules based on signal pattern so that the correct detection of R-peaks is possible even with a change in the pattern
elements.2211.03171_9a4f008558689f9eac1f497d121c5: We tested our proposed algorithm on four open-source ECG datasets- MIT-BIH Arrhythmia Dataset, St.-Petersburg Institute of Cardiological Technics 12-lead Arrhythmia Dataset, European ST-T Dataset, and Computing in Cardiology Challenge 2014 Dataset

elements.2211.03171_373a0a69f20c2510407b495a7f35e: The European ST-T Dataset consists of 90 two hour annotated records of two-channel (III, V4) from 79 subjects
elements.2211.03171_11c21d42dce6868d0a65d04c34e2b: The first 40 minutes of each record have been taken for evaluation as it would take a long time to evaluate the entire record
elements.2211.03171_4b88282da4726c05a2a2b83738fb5: From the Pan-Tompkins algorithm, a major improvement is observed with the proposed algorithm for records from both of the channels (Table IV)
elements.2211.03171_125224f1a625275abd842b99d72a9: For lead-III, the PPV, sensitivity, and F-score increase by 5.29, 5.52, and 5.4 percent, respectively
elements.2211.03171_5dd8cdb022955c8401c153c48e959: In records 116, 119, 205, 206, 405, 602, 605, 611, 613, and 817, the Pan-Tompkins algorithm fails to detect R-peaks when the signal changes its usual pattern
elements.2211.03171_da49f15852d25bcd97da905aebb96: Pan-Tompkins++ detects those R-peaks as it considers the preceding and following signal components from the current position
elements.2211.03171_560870b344826b2685bb519edc196: The Computing in Cardiology Challenge 2014 Dataset consists of 100 ten-minute annotated recordings from lead II
elements.2211.03171_e6b99b0a6aedd42bbfd01f8a8b753: Here, all the algorithms perform poorly when compared to the other datasets
elements.2211.03171_ec0059af4fe8840aca14d71ff3248: However, Pan-Tompkins++ outperforms all the other algorithms by a significant margin (Table V)
elements.2211.03171_bf84bfb93bf82d7899e03f8a24d2c: There are some R-peaks with exceptionally high magnitude found in records 1028, 1522, 1683, 1715, 1804, 2201, 2203, 2370, and 2664
elements.2211.03171_13ac20363eb869314f70ec6f702af: The Pan-Tompkins algorithm could not detect true R-peaks for a long period of time after those high R-peaks as the thresholds became high
elements.2211.03171_70111e3ac7fb32fd5e466686bc5c2: Pan-Tompkins++ successfully detects those true R-peaks because it compares peaks with a reduced threshold when there is no R-peak detected in recent 1.4s
elements.2211.03171_702ee716f5ae58cde515baed112d5: The improvement over the Pan-Tompkins algorithm is notable for PPV and execution time
elements.2211.03171_10ec6a97dea08e48155d164dfe1e7: Figure 6 illustrates a situation where Pan-Tompkins++ (PT++) effectively detects the true R-peaks while all the other algorithms fail
elements.2211.03171_b383560967426a65d107f1bf24b4d: Hamilton (Ham), Modified Engzee (ME), Wavelet Transform (WT), and Two Moving Averages (TMA) algorithms detect false R-peaks (blue x) as they find sharp transitions apart from the true QRS complex
elements.2211.03171_91347f5e271a4b72eeb8d187e9808: Pan-Tompkins (PT) identifies both false (blue x) and true (red circle) R-peaks
elements.2211.03171_97dce7772af2d6b5fc4e92bceb83f: Pan-Tompkins++ (PT++) successfully detects only the real R-peaks (red circle) as it compares the morphology of the current candidate QRS complex with that of the most recent detected beat over a 70ms window, and there is a 231ms refractory period once a valid QRS complex is found
elements.2211.03171_efd3c8c1f0a03d13fcef2ca29e371: Pan-Tompkins++ outperforms all the selected classical algorithms for each of the four datasets
elements.2211.03171_db398cd0c6d367713d3e8224f44f4: There is a significant reduction in execution time, which makes the algorithm more suitable for real-time heart monitoring applications
elements.2211.03171_ccc1ba54bd77fd58f66d1fad04422: One of the reasons for the reduction of execution time is that there is a 231ms refractory period following the identification of a valid QRS complex before the next one can be found, as we allow a maximum heart rate of 260 bpm
elements.2211.03171_fcf790cb466c378a95425c331be8e: It is 200ms in the Pan-Tompkins algorithm
elements.2211.03171_66702dd416d2f2f87308a1a5e214a: Moreover, in the Pan-Tompkins algorithm, the thresholds are adjusted whenever the current RR-interval is less than 92
elements.2211.03171_bef453aa8b5a622a0a2f9626585a6: This adjustment has been removed as there was no improvement found with it
elements.2211.03171_67775777d99e58ab7a5cd7b9a3a4f: It is important to note that although the performance of these algorithms seem high, there is still room for improvement, even for Pan-Tompkins++
elements.2211.03171_75cd3cf93632217fd2af159954e70: Even a small number of false or missed detections can result in misdiagnosis or cardiac events with catastrophic consequences.
elements.2211.03171_398e8d13b0e5e73ec93ad56ba648e: In this paper, we presented Pan-Tompkins++, inspired by the Pan-Tompkins algorithm, for better R-peak detection in ECG
elements.2211.03171_12eb2a013230c69a97211d69c1345: The preprocessing and thresholding approaches were chosen to enhance true R-peak detection
elements.2211.03171_d9d83a7e9e00a8f913cf6ae7cae5c: This would do away with the requirement for a separate filtering function altogether
elements.2211.03171_1a7d9c1160777e815e0bd3c71c4cb: The proposed algorithm greatly improves the performance of the Pan-Tompkins algorithm
